President Obama spoke with Crown Prince Mohammed bin Zayed Al Nahyan of the United Arab Emirates (UAE) regarding the situation in Egypt. Both leaders expressed their concerns about the violence and political polarization in Egypt and emphasized the need for all Egyptian leaders to discourage violence and avoid incitement. They agreed that for Egypt to overcome the crisis, all Egyptians must come together and find a path towards inclusivity. President Obama urged all political, military, and religious leaders in Egypt to engage in dialogue and commit to a political process in order to facilitate the return to a democratically elected civilian government. He also asked the UAE to emphasize the importance of avoiding violence and promoting dialogue and reconciliation in their interactions with Egyptians. President Obama expressed his gratitude for the strong partnership and friendship between the US and the UAE and extended his wishes to the Crown Prince for Ramadan.